      "description": "Available for the discerning collector is an exceptional 1997 Mazda RX-7 (FD3S), a masterclass in lightweight engineering and balanced dynamics. This example features the iconic 13B-REW sequential twin-turbocharged rotary engine, delivering seamless boost throughout the rev range. The powerplant is mated to a precise five-speed short-throw manual transmission and a factory Torsen limited-slip differential, ensuring optimal torque vectoring. Its lightweight aluminum double-wishbone suspension and 50/50 weight distribution provide unparalleled steering feedback and lateral grip. Preserved in a concours-ready state, this vehicle remains entirely stock, with all vacuum lines, apex seals, and thermal management systems maintained to factory specifications. The interior ergonomics and exterior finish are flawless, representing a rare opportunity to own a pure, unmolested JDM legend.",
